Package: mixology
Title: Sentiment Analysis Lexicons and Tools for Crisis Communication Research
Version: 0.3.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Laurence", "Dierickx", email = "hello@ohmybox.info", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-5926-8720"))
Description: Provides eight sentiment lexicons and a reproducible analytical
    pipeline for comparative opinion mining in crisis communication research.
    Includes two manually annotated domain-specific lexicons developed for the
    Mixology project (Covid-19 political measures, Western Europe, December 2021)
    and six harmonised general-purpose English sentiment dictionaries: General
    Inquirer, MPQA Subjectivity Lexicon, Bing Liu, NRC Emotion Lexicon, AFINN,
    and Loughran-McDonald. All lexicons share a common three-category polarity
    scheme (positive, negative, ambiguous), enabling direct cross-lexicon
    comparison. Also includes a domain-specific stop word list, negation markers,
    and functions for tokenisation, negation-aware scoring, weighted sentiment
    analysis, coverage diagnostics, and polarity conflict detection. Companion
    package to Dierickx (2026) <doi:10.XXXX/XXXXXX>.
